WEBVTT

00:00:13.221 --> 00:00:15.265
Everyone put out your hands...

00:00:19.978 --> 00:00:21.855
Focus your Spiritual Pressure
into those orbs.

00:00:42.667 --> 00:00:44.919
"UNKNOWN ANOMALY DETECTED"

00:00:44.919 --> 00:00:45.879
"UNKNOWN ANOMALY DETECTED"
What was that?

00:00:45.879 --> 00:00:45.920
What was that?

00:00:46.254 --> 00:00:47.839
What is going on?

00:00:49.841 --> 00:00:50.842
What the...

00:00:56.723 --> 00:00:57.974
No way...

00:00:58.058 --> 00:00:59.726
What the hell is going on?

00:01:00.226 --> 00:01:03.688
The Wandenreich cityscape
covering the Seireitei

00:01:03.772 --> 00:01:04.814
is being stripped away...!

00:01:07.192 --> 00:01:09.736
But why?
Why is this happening?

00:01:10.487 --> 00:01:12.781
What are the Quincies
trying to do?!

00:01:13.323 --> 00:01:14.491
Oh, come on!

00:01:14.866 --> 00:01:19.746
And here we're just getting started
on building one measly gate...

00:01:20.246 --> 00:01:23.208
Don't our enemies have any limits
to what they can do?!

00:01:30.715 --> 00:01:32.258
This can't be good...

00:01:32.592 --> 00:01:34.678
We need to hurry
and finish up the gate!

00:01:47.649 --> 00:01:52.696
I put my hands together and pray

00:01:52.821 --> 00:01:58.076
Why is fate so cruel?

00:01:58.159 --> 00:02:03.581
My will to put on a brave face
is about to break

00:02:03.665 --> 00:02:08.753
Everything I do seems to go wrong,
you know?

00:02:09.004 --> 00:02:11.589
Oh, calm down,
I still have faith in you

00:02:11.631 --> 00:02:14.467
Even if we're apart

00:02:14.509 --> 00:02:21.683
Even if you forget about me someday

00:02:22.559 --> 00:02:24.352
BLEACH: THOUSAND-YEAR BLOOD WAR

00:02:25.020 --> 00:02:27.355
We don't need words
to understand each other

00:02:27.397 --> 00:02:30.316
We're connected on a higher level

00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:35.280
I'm sorry, fate,
but you're full of it

00:02:35.363 --> 00:02:37.866
So let's laugh it off
by putting on a brave face

00:02:37.949 --> 00:02:45.498
With you, I think we can alter fate

00:02:45.832 --> 00:02:51.129
On lonely nights
when I feel like crying

00:02:51.171 --> 00:02:55.008
I will pray for you

00:02:55.133 --> 00:02:57.969
so that I won't leave you all alone

00:03:19.824 --> 00:03:20.825
Open it!

00:03:27.374 --> 00:03:28.375
You're...

00:03:29.042 --> 00:03:32.212
Hey. It's been a while, Kurosaki.

00:03:32.962 --> 00:03:34.005
Grimmjow!

00:03:39.010 --> 00:03:40.303
How many years has it been?

00:03:40.720 --> 00:03:43.348
Looks like the wound I gave you
in our last battle has healed.

00:03:43.932 --> 00:03:47.310
You're damn right.
You're looking good yourself.

00:03:47.936 --> 00:03:49.813
Did you think I was dead?

00:03:55.527 --> 00:03:58.405
Like I'd die before killing you.

00:03:59.030 --> 00:04:00.990
I've been waiting for this moment...

00:04:01.366 --> 00:04:03.702
where I can settle
the score with you-

00:04:05.954 --> 00:04:08.039
Ichigo!

00:04:08.415 --> 00:04:11.793
- N-Nel?!
- I missed you so much, Ichigo!

00:04:14.004 --> 00:04:16.047
Mr. Urahara made a bracelet

00:04:16.131 --> 00:04:19.718
that lets me switch between
a kid and an adult at will!

00:04:20.051 --> 00:04:23.430
Now I can finally be of
actual help to you, Ichigo!

00:04:24.055 --> 00:04:26.433
In fact, I may never go back
to being a kid

00:04:26.558 --> 00:04:28.101
as long as I have this bracelet!

00:04:28.852 --> 00:04:29.853
Inoue...

00:04:29.894 --> 00:04:31.187
You're probably thinking,

00:04:31.229 --> 00:04:33.398
"Why does he have to keep making
unnecessary things..."

00:04:34.524 --> 00:04:37.694
But don't think like that.
Urahara's doing the best he can...

00:04:37.902 --> 00:04:40.113
D-Don't be silly, Sado...

00:04:40.238 --> 00:04:42.699
I would never think of that!
Really!

00:04:42.907 --> 00:04:44.909
Nelliel, what's the big idea?!

00:04:45.035 --> 00:04:46.578
Get lost, you're in my way!

00:04:47.370 --> 00:04:48.413
That's my line.

00:04:48.997 --> 00:04:52.042
If you're only here to start a fight,
then stay out of it.

00:04:54.044 --> 00:04:55.920
Need I remind you that I'm No.3?

00:04:56.004 --> 00:04:58.882
I don't take orders
from a No.6 like you.

00:04:59.007 --> 00:05:00.175
Bullshit.

00:05:00.425 --> 00:05:03.970
Those numbers mean nothing
now that Aizen's gone.

00:05:04.471 --> 00:05:06.890
In fact, why don't we
find out right now

00:05:06.973 --> 00:05:09.142
to see which one of us is superior!

00:05:09.768 --> 00:05:11.936
- Grimmjow, wait-!
- Testing, testing...

00:05:12.187 --> 00:05:13.438
Okay, cut it out!

00:05:13.521 --> 00:05:16.066
Seriously,
are there only idiots here?

00:05:16.274 --> 00:05:18.485
This isn't what we came here for,
remember?!

00:05:19.903 --> 00:05:20.904
That voice...

00:05:21.071 --> 00:05:23.948
Will you hurry up and get inside
before they see us?

00:05:25.492 --> 00:05:27.118
And that box...could it be...?

00:05:27.911 --> 00:05:30.330
I said, hurry up and get inside!

00:05:30.705 --> 00:05:31.706
Riruka?!

00:05:32.165 --> 00:05:33.750
I'm here, too, you know.

00:05:33.833 --> 00:05:34.834
Yukio!

00:05:34.959 --> 00:05:37.128
Oh, and in case it wasn't
already obvious,

00:05:37.170 --> 00:05:38.922
this is my ability
you're looking at.

00:05:39.214 --> 00:05:41.049
I knew you guys were alive!

00:05:41.591 --> 00:05:44.052
Hold on,
what are you doing here anyway?

00:05:44.636 --> 00:05:48.014
Just get in for now.
We'll explain inside.

00:05:51.935 --> 00:05:52.936
So...

00:05:53.103 --> 00:05:55.105
which part do you need me
to explain, Ichigo?

00:05:55.480 --> 00:05:56.564
Are you kidding me?

00:05:56.690 --> 00:05:56.731
GARGANTA - INSIDE YUKIO'S BOX

00:05:56.731 --> 00:06:01.444
GARGANTA - INSIDE YUKIO'S BOX
What do you mean, "which part"?!
You need to explain everything!

00:06:01.820 --> 00:06:03.988
And I mean everything!

00:06:04.531 --> 00:06:06.199
We're so lost here!
Right, guys?

00:06:06.783 --> 00:06:09.661
Actually, we were told
while at Hueco Mundo...

00:06:10.036 --> 00:06:11.037
Sorry...

00:06:13.540 --> 00:06:15.917
Oh, so you guys already
knew back then...

00:06:16.251 --> 00:06:18.878
The more manpower we have,
the better, right?

00:06:19.087 --> 00:06:20.505
Yeah, but isn't it wrong that

00:06:20.588 --> 00:06:22.966
I'm the only one
left out of the loop?

00:06:23.299 --> 00:06:24.300
True...

00:06:24.509 --> 00:06:27.470
Well, you've been
quite busy lately, so...

00:06:27.595 --> 00:06:29.639
Hey, don't give me that tired look!

00:06:29.931 --> 00:06:30.974
There was no time.

00:06:31.099 --> 00:06:33.643
Oh, really?
I think we had plenty of time-

00:06:33.685 --> 00:06:35.061
like on our way here!

00:06:36.855 --> 00:06:38.148
"WORLD OF THE LIVING / SOUL SOCIETY"

00:06:38.148 --> 00:06:39.983
"WORLD OF THE LIVING / SOUL SOCIETY"
The Precipice World connects
the Soul Society

00:06:39.983 --> 00:06:40.066
"WORLD OF THE LIVING / SOUL SOCIETY"

00:06:40.066 --> 00:06:41.317
"WORLD OF THE LIVING / SOUL SOCIETY"
and the World of the Living.

00:06:41.359 --> 00:06:41.609
- That, you know.
- Yeah.

00:06:41.609 --> 00:06:43.319
"PRECIPICE WORLD"
- That, you know.
- Yeah.

00:06:43.695 --> 00:06:45.113
Scattered around
the Precipice World

00:06:45.155 --> 00:06:48.700
are areas of various sizes
known as the Valley of Screams

00:06:48.742 --> 00:06:49.993
where lost souls exist.

00:06:50.493 --> 00:06:53.038
Garganta exists
to fill up the empty space

00:06:53.121 --> 00:06:54.622
in between these areas.

00:06:55.331 --> 00:06:58.626
Spiritual Pressure becomes unstable
while inside Garganta.

00:06:58.918 --> 00:07:01.212
One can barely stand
without constantly releasing

00:07:01.338 --> 00:07:04.007
their Spiritual Pressure
to create a foothold.

00:07:04.966 --> 00:07:07.677
But the Valley of Screams
seems to be an exception.

00:07:08.011 --> 00:07:10.847
It can somehow exist inside
as a Reishi space

00:07:10.930 --> 00:07:13.641
due to its different
Reishi structure.

00:07:14.142 --> 00:07:17.145
Kisuke decided to use that
to our advantage.

00:07:18.730 --> 00:07:22.025
That's why we found
and brought these two back.

00:07:22.901 --> 00:07:24.903
- Still can't believe they found us.
- Her ability to move a target

00:07:24.903 --> 00:07:26.863
- Still can't believe they found us.
- in and out of her favorite objects...

00:07:27.238 --> 00:07:29.741
and his ability
to create his own dimension

00:07:29.783 --> 00:07:30.992
using electricity.

00:07:31.576 --> 00:07:34.454
That's not really how it works.
But whatever...

00:07:35.080 --> 00:07:39.417
We used Riruka's ability to carry
a small Valley of Screams in a box,

00:07:39.584 --> 00:07:42.921
then modified it into a room
with rails using Yukio's ability.

00:07:43.421 --> 00:07:46.633
We were finally able to
complete it just now.

00:07:46.966 --> 00:07:49.969
However, we're only able to
move the short distance

00:07:50.053 --> 00:07:53.890
from here to the stake I placed
as a marker in the Royal Palace.

00:07:54.683 --> 00:07:56.893
Still, the benefits of
entering enemy territory

00:07:56.935 --> 00:07:58.895
without using
Spiritual Pressure are huge!

00:07:59.396 --> 00:08:01.606
We can mount a surprise attack now.

00:08:02.399 --> 00:08:04.609
We'll take them down
in one shot, Ichigo!

00:08:16.162 --> 00:08:18.081
Hey, something's not right.

00:08:18.331 --> 00:08:20.208
The gate we just built
is disappearing...

00:08:20.291 --> 00:08:22.002
What is going on?

00:08:22.460 --> 00:08:23.920
It's lacking
Spiritual Pressure...!

00:08:24.129 --> 00:08:25.130
What?

00:08:25.255 --> 00:08:27.048
We needed Captain Ukitake...

00:08:27.132 --> 00:08:29.509
No other captain
could come close to

00:08:29.592 --> 00:08:32.262
the Spiritual Pressure
he possess...

00:08:32.971 --> 00:08:33.930
At this rate...

00:08:36.599 --> 00:08:37.976
At this rate, what?

00:08:39.060 --> 00:08:40.353
It's not over yet.

00:08:41.604 --> 00:08:42.772
Ms. Yadomaru...

00:08:44.065 --> 00:08:45.734
We put on the Shihakusho!

00:08:45.942 --> 00:08:49.029
Hurry up and give us our damn orbs,
Kisuke!

00:08:55.160 --> 00:08:59.122
The numbers show we clearly
lack enough Spiritual Pressure.

00:08:59.122 --> 00:09:03.168
So why aren't you using
the Spiritual Pressure amplifier?

00:09:09.966 --> 00:09:13.553
Why didn't you tell us
you had such a thing?

00:09:13.970 --> 00:09:18.475
Because I never anticipated
it would come to this.

00:09:36.201 --> 00:09:39.913
I won't let your sacrifice
go in vain, Ukitake...

00:09:43.041 --> 00:09:46.211
We'll ascend to the Royal Palace
and mount a surprise attack.

00:09:47.045 --> 00:09:49.172
While attempting
to seal the Soul King,

00:09:49.339 --> 00:09:52.884
I drove in a stake near him
just like the one below.

00:09:53.343 --> 00:09:54.969
If they haven't moved,

00:09:55.053 --> 00:09:57.097
we should be able to arrive
right in front of them.

00:09:57.681 --> 00:09:59.474
Use that split moment
to strike Yhwach

00:09:59.557 --> 00:10:01.643
with your most powerful Getsuga.

00:10:02.060 --> 00:10:04.521
I know you can do this, Ichigo.

00:10:05.355 --> 00:10:06.356
Got it.

00:10:06.690 --> 00:10:10.193
We'll clear the path of anyone
who gets in your way.

00:10:10.652 --> 00:10:12.696
Leave the minions to us!

00:10:12.904 --> 00:10:14.114
Right, I'm counting on you.

00:10:14.572 --> 00:10:16.908
We have a good grasp of
the Royal Guards' powers,

00:10:17.200 --> 00:10:19.411
but what exactly are Yhwach's?

00:10:23.915 --> 00:10:26.918
I wish we had asked Osho
more about it.

00:10:27.669 --> 00:10:28.670
So annoying!

00:10:29.045 --> 00:10:31.006
I'm totally lost here.

00:10:31.297 --> 00:10:36.094
I don't know what happened,
but stop moping about the past!

00:10:36.970 --> 00:10:40.682
I hate that you're making us
feel gloomy, too!

00:10:41.891 --> 00:10:45.061
You're right.
Thank you, Riruka!

00:10:45.145 --> 00:10:47.814
Why are you thanking me for that?!
You're such a weirdo!

00:10:49.107 --> 00:10:50.108
By the way...

00:10:50.692 --> 00:10:53.945
Why are you on our side, Grimmjow?

00:10:54.404 --> 00:10:57.282
Huh? Who said I'm on your side?

00:10:57.490 --> 00:10:58.950
What an idiot...

00:10:59.576 --> 00:11:03.872
If we let that Yhwach have his way,
Hueco Mundo will be gone.

00:11:04.414 --> 00:11:08.501
If Hueco Mundo is gone,
where am I supposed to kill you?

00:11:11.921 --> 00:11:13.131
You have a point.

00:11:30.940 --> 00:11:33.068
My sons...

00:11:40.283 --> 00:11:41.326
What's wrong?

00:11:41.701 --> 00:11:43.203
Calm down, Nakk Le Vaar.

00:11:43.661 --> 00:11:45.997
Seriously?
What is wrong with this guy?!

00:11:46.122 --> 00:11:47.499
Doesn't he feel anything

00:11:47.540 --> 00:11:50.293
from seeing His Majesty
looking like a monster?!

00:11:50.919 --> 00:11:52.545
Do I scare you?

00:11:53.171 --> 00:11:55.006
Don't be so afraid.

00:11:55.382 --> 00:11:57.759
In time, you will get used to
my appearance.

00:11:58.927 --> 00:12:01.429
Ah, so this...

00:12:02.055 --> 00:12:06.643
this is what it's like to be
overflowing with power.

00:12:21.157 --> 00:12:23.868
We're dead if we fall from here!

00:12:23.993 --> 00:12:26.621
Hey! How can you be so calm,
Haschwal-?

00:12:33.044 --> 00:12:34.379
No way...

00:12:45.682 --> 00:12:47.600
Such magnificent power.

00:12:47.809 --> 00:12:49.644
The world where
the Soul King is gone

00:12:49.686 --> 00:12:52.022
cannot exist without
Your Majesty's powers.

00:12:53.398 --> 00:12:55.567
Guide us, Your Majesty.

00:12:56.901 --> 00:13:00.613
Haschwalth, my first son.

00:13:01.197 --> 00:13:04.909
Stand behind me
and watch the path I take.

00:13:06.077 --> 00:13:09.998
I shall begin
by reinventing our nation.

00:13:36.107 --> 00:13:38.485
We're almost there.
Are you guys ready?

00:13:38.818 --> 00:13:39.819
Yeah.

00:13:39.944 --> 00:13:41.404
Just for the record...

00:13:42.113 --> 00:13:44.532
I have no intention of
leaving this place.

00:13:44.908 --> 00:13:46.534
Do whatever you want
without me.

00:13:47.243 --> 00:13:48.953
What are you talking about?

00:13:49.204 --> 00:13:51.373
Look, I don't know
who you are, but-

00:13:51.373 --> 00:13:53.750
And I don't know you, either.

00:13:54.417 --> 00:13:57.420
They introduced themselves
earlier, right?

00:13:57.921 --> 00:14:02.008
Ganju did, but Yukio ignored him.

00:14:02.258 --> 00:14:04.886
I don't care who you are,
but let me say this!

00:14:05.136 --> 00:14:10.266
We're about to fight for our lives,
and you're just gonna stay here?

00:14:10.433 --> 00:14:12.727
I was dragged into this.

00:14:13.269 --> 00:14:15.188
I'm not obligated to risk my life.

00:14:15.355 --> 00:14:18.316
Risking your life out of obligation
isn't risking at all!

00:14:18.650 --> 00:14:20.735
You can hide here and do whatever.

00:14:20.860 --> 00:14:24.364
But if we lose,
this Garganta will be gone, too!

00:14:25.156 --> 00:14:26.157
Do you plan on losing?

00:14:27.075 --> 00:14:28.201
That's enough, Ganju.

00:14:28.993 --> 00:14:31.246
He got you.
You lose.

00:14:31.955 --> 00:14:34.207
Yukio, you stay here.

00:14:34.457 --> 00:14:36.960
I thought that's what I said.

00:14:37.419 --> 00:14:38.169
You too, Riruka.

00:14:39.129 --> 00:14:40.130
Stay here.

00:14:40.422 --> 00:14:41.423
What?!

00:14:42.007 --> 00:14:43.425
It's for your own good.

00:14:43.425 --> 00:14:46.428
Your abilities will not be enough
to survive this battle.

00:14:46.678 --> 00:14:48.096
No way, you can't be serious-

00:14:48.138 --> 00:14:50.390
I've been to
the Valley of Screams before.

00:14:51.307 --> 00:14:53.226
I know how much
you love cute stuff.

00:14:53.768 --> 00:14:56.271
And that you can only put
things you love into your box.

00:14:56.980 --> 00:14:59.441
The Valley of Screams
is anything but cute.

00:14:59.774 --> 00:15:01.609
There's no way you could
stuff it into a box.

00:15:02.902 --> 00:15:05.113
You went out of your way
just for us, didn't you?

00:15:06.114 --> 00:15:07.115
Thanks.

00:15:08.700 --> 00:15:10.535
N-No, why would I do that-!

00:15:10.618 --> 00:15:14.289
So do us one more favor, will you?

00:15:15.165 --> 00:15:20.170
Stay here with Yukio and be ready
to get us out at any time.

00:15:22.339 --> 00:15:23.673
Why should I...?

00:15:25.675 --> 00:15:26.760
Okay, fine...

00:15:28.345 --> 00:15:29.429
Hey, Ichigo.

00:15:30.513 --> 00:15:30.722
You've grown up.

00:15:30.722 --> 00:15:32.766
You've grown up.

00:15:33.391 --> 00:15:34.976
Really? How so?

00:15:36.603 --> 00:15:38.855
Well, maybe not.

00:15:39.564 --> 00:15:42.400
I guess you've always
been that way.

00:15:58.333 --> 00:15:59.501
It's ready!

00:16:07.425 --> 00:16:08.385
We've arrived.

00:16:09.803 --> 00:16:10.845
Let's go.

00:16:11.096 --> 00:16:12.097
Right.

00:16:23.358 --> 00:16:27.362
Beyond this gate
is the Royal Palace.

00:16:28.321 --> 00:16:30.865
Thanks, everybody.
Wish us luck!

00:16:31.658 --> 00:16:32.659
- Sir!
- Sir!

00:16:33.952 --> 00:16:37.038
I'm opening the gate!
Is everyone ready?

00:16:37.247 --> 00:16:38.331
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

00:16:49.843 --> 00:16:51.136
What is this place?!

00:16:51.594 --> 00:16:52.971
This isn't the Royal Palace...

00:16:53.471 --> 00:16:56.141
This cityscape is that of a Quincy...

00:16:56.307 --> 00:16:59.019
Wait a minute...
Then where the hell are we?

00:17:03.356 --> 00:17:05.525
W-What is all this?!

00:17:05.859 --> 00:17:07.736
I thought we were
entering the Royal Palace.

00:17:07.902 --> 00:17:09.821
How did we end up in a Quincy town?

00:17:10.655 --> 00:17:12.115
What's going on, Kisuke!

00:17:12.282 --> 00:17:14.117
Weren't we supposed to be
at the Royal Palace?!

00:17:14.242 --> 00:17:17.120
Our coordinates place us
right above the Seireitei.

00:17:17.370 --> 00:17:19.330
We should be at the Royal Palace.

00:17:19.456 --> 00:17:20.457
Impossible...!

00:17:20.582 --> 00:17:23.251
Did we not arrive at the spot
where I drove the stake in?

00:17:33.136 --> 00:17:34.137
Ichigo...

00:17:34.637 --> 00:17:35.638
So in other words,

00:17:35.680 --> 00:17:38.183
the town that was lifted from
the Seireitei earlier

00:17:38.266 --> 00:17:41.478
was rebuilt atop
a demolished Royal Palace.

00:17:41.561 --> 00:17:44.147
No way! That was moments ago,
how could-

00:17:44.230 --> 00:17:45.231
Exactly...

00:17:46.024 --> 00:17:50.362
That's how powerful our enemy
has become.

00:17:56.034 --> 00:17:57.035
Ichigo...

00:18:01.498 --> 00:18:04.626
Looks like this place is definitely
the Royal Palace.

00:18:07.337 --> 00:18:12.509
That damn Yhwach...he rebuilt
the Royal Palace to his own liking.

00:18:14.386 --> 00:18:17.847
Take a look.
The edge of the town is a circle.

00:18:18.056 --> 00:18:21.226
This area is probably
one of Squad Zero's Riden

00:18:21.267 --> 00:18:22.894
in the Royal Palace.

00:18:23.311 --> 00:18:27.357
But we can't see the Royal Palace
that should be floating above it.

00:18:27.941 --> 00:18:29.234
So what you're saying is...

00:18:29.734 --> 00:18:31.903
that the Royal Palace
was brought down

00:18:31.945 --> 00:18:34.406
and everything of it
fell into enemy hands?

00:18:35.365 --> 00:18:37.784
I-Is that even possible...?

00:18:38.326 --> 00:18:41.204
We were spared
getting caught in that event

00:18:41.287 --> 00:18:43.123
thanks to our being
in the Garganta.

00:18:43.873 --> 00:18:45.625
We should consider ourselves lucky.

00:18:47.752 --> 00:18:49.337
My sister's Spiritual Pressure!

00:18:49.879 --> 00:18:52.215
This Spiritual Pressure is from...
Yushiro?

00:18:52.716 --> 00:18:53.717
Who?

00:18:54.175 --> 00:18:55.552
Yushiro Shihoin.

00:18:55.760 --> 00:18:59.347
My younger brother who became
head of the Shihoin Clan

00:18:59.389 --> 00:19:00.849
after I was banished.

00:19:01.099 --> 00:19:04.227
Y-Yoruichi, you have a brother?
Why didn't you tell me?!

00:19:04.561 --> 00:19:08.106
And why should I bother telling you
I have a younger brother?

00:19:08.273 --> 00:19:10.191
What are you, my fiancé?

00:19:10.442 --> 00:19:12.944
I'll be right there, Sister!

00:19:14.112 --> 00:19:15.113
Huh?!

00:19:17.615 --> 00:19:20.744
Y-You idiot!
What were you thinking?!

00:19:20.827 --> 00:19:25.331
Sorry... I can't seem to create
a foothold for some reason.

00:19:25.498 --> 00:19:30.170
It seems finding a foothold
with Reishi here won't be easy.

00:19:30.337 --> 00:19:31.713
What do you mean, sir?

00:19:32.339 --> 00:19:34.132
I'm sure you're feeling it too,

00:19:34.507 --> 00:19:36.926
but the Reishi density in
the Royal Palace's atmosphere

00:19:37.010 --> 00:19:38.303
is quite high.

00:19:39.304 --> 00:19:40.305
True...

00:19:41.264 --> 00:19:43.641
Ordinarily, it should be easy
to create a foothold

00:19:43.767 --> 00:19:45.518
with this kind of Reishi density.

00:19:46.269 --> 00:19:48.605
Which leaves only one reason
why we can't.

00:19:49.397 --> 00:19:54.569
The enemy side holds control of
all of the Reishi in this area.

00:19:55.570 --> 00:19:58.615
It makes sense for them
to prepare a battlefield

00:19:58.698 --> 00:20:00.575
that works to our disadvantage.

00:20:00.867 --> 00:20:02.202
Quincies can manipulate

00:20:02.285 --> 00:20:04.829
and use the Reishi
in their surroundings.

00:20:05.121 --> 00:20:08.833
It'd be something
their leader would do.

00:20:09.918 --> 00:20:13.171
Especially one
who can kill the Soul King.

00:20:13.588 --> 00:20:14.589
You're right...

00:20:15.090 --> 00:20:19.678
Since coming here, I haven't sensed
the Soul King's Spiritual Pressure.

00:20:20.428 --> 00:20:23.348
Does this mean he was killed,
after all?

00:20:23.807 --> 00:20:25.183
Now, now...

00:20:25.266 --> 00:20:26.726
They're far away,

00:20:26.810 --> 00:20:29.979
but I can feel the Spiritual Pressure
of Ichigo's party.

00:20:30.355 --> 00:20:33.608
The fact that our advance troops
weren't wiped out is good news.

00:20:34.275 --> 00:20:36.611
If the Soul King died
at the hands of the enemy,

00:20:36.695 --> 00:20:40.156
then we need to defeat the enemy
and decide on a new Soul King.

00:20:40.865 --> 00:20:44.577
If Ukitake could talk,
he'd probably say the same thing.

00:20:46.329 --> 00:20:47.330
Let's get going.

00:20:48.081 --> 00:20:50.166
If we can't rendezvous
with Ichigo's party,

00:20:50.291 --> 00:20:52.335
we must proceed
on the path we're given.

00:20:53.003 --> 00:20:54.838
We're the 13 Court Guard Squads.

00:20:55.338 --> 00:20:57.632
So let's advance for the sake of
the Court Guard.

00:20:58.133 --> 00:20:59.175
- Yes, sir!
- Right!

00:21:01.511 --> 00:21:02.679
Yeep!

00:21:04.180 --> 00:21:05.348
Now what?

00:21:20.280 --> 00:21:21.656
What is that?!

00:21:21.740 --> 00:21:23.366
Come on, isn't it obvious?

00:21:23.408 --> 00:21:26.161
That's our enemy's stronghold.

00:21:26.619 --> 00:21:29.164
Not only are they not
running and hiding...

00:21:29.330 --> 00:21:32.417
it's almost as if
they're inviting us.

00:21:32.709 --> 00:21:34.127
Indeed.

00:21:35.337 --> 00:21:37.380
They sure got nerves...

00:21:42.385 --> 00:21:43.595
Your Majesty...

00:21:44.262 --> 00:21:45.930
It appears
Ichigo Kurosaki's party

00:21:46.056 --> 00:21:48.141
and the 13 Court Guard Squads

00:21:48.224 --> 00:21:51.102
have arrived simultaneously
at this...

00:21:51.227 --> 00:21:52.312
Welt.

00:21:53.605 --> 00:21:58.151
This castle has become
the foundation for a new world.

00:21:58.360 --> 00:22:00.945
The one and only true world.

00:22:01.821 --> 00:22:04.991
It will one day
be known as Wahr Welt.

00:22:05.533 --> 00:22:08.912
Then we shall kill
every last one of them.

00:22:09.621 --> 00:22:12.665
To realize the future that is
reflected in Your Majesty's eyes.

00:22:13.249 --> 00:22:15.835
Here, at the foundation
of the new world...

00:22:16.920 --> 00:22:18.380
at Wahr Welt.

00:22:31.559 --> 00:22:35.146
An ache upon
an unsatisfying grayscale

00:22:35.230 --> 00:22:39.109
My confidence vanishes

00:22:45.782 --> 00:22:47.200
I turned regret into lies

00:22:47.200 --> 00:22:49.202
I ignored our chipped blades

00:22:49.285 --> 00:22:50.912
I worked overtime
just for maintenance

00:22:50.995 --> 00:22:52.914
But I knew all along

00:22:52.956 --> 00:22:56.334
that this faded color
was an irreversible law

00:22:56.334 --> 00:22:58.211
So I might as well pray

00:22:58.294 --> 00:23:00.088
There's no turning back now

00:23:00.130 --> 00:23:01.965
I thought I had made up my mind

00:23:02.090 --> 00:23:03.758
but I'm still haunted by
doubt and anxiety

00:23:03.883 --> 00:23:05.427
A bundle of emotions torn to shreds

00:23:05.552 --> 00:23:07.303
with nothing left for me to gain

00:23:07.429 --> 00:23:11.266
What's more important
than one's life

00:23:11.307 --> 00:23:14.144
is to shoulder that burden
to sever this monochrome

00:23:14.144 --> 00:23:19.149
I keep searching for the answer
to an unsolvable thesis

00:23:19.232 --> 00:23:21.276
while making choices until I die

00:23:21.359 --> 00:23:25.405
Then I remember where we came from

00:23:25.488 --> 00:23:28.324
and the lives
that could never interact

00:23:28.408 --> 00:23:32.037
No one is allowed to use the scale
since it falls apart in an instant

00:23:32.120 --> 00:23:35.457
So, what can I measure
ourselves against?

00:23:35.540 --> 00:23:39.753
Instead, I hold onto your words

00:23:39.836 --> 00:23:42.589
that gave my heart meaning

00:23:42.630 --> 00:23:43.882
It's always a paradox

00:23:43.965 --> 00:23:45.967
The moon waxes
with each regret and sadness

00:23:46.092 --> 00:23:49.679
The massive, unconquerable foe is
the darkness that dwells within me

00:23:49.804 --> 00:23:51.389
I forsook my pride and joy

00:23:51.514 --> 00:23:53.141
but I am still confounded
by this flock of imperfection

00:23:53.224 --> 00:23:55.060
Beyond that white and resentful
midnight sun

00:23:55.101 --> 00:23:57.145
awaits an illusion etched in black

00:24:03.401 --> 00:24:06.237
"The fire that drips from fangs
does not fade."

00:24:07.238 --> 00:24:09.741
"The blade burns away the field."

00:24:10.992 --> 00:24:13.953
"Revealing my hidden friend."

